        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-18 14:17:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nThanks for the work Dominik, I think there is no changes to do in both policy/drools-pdp and policy/drools-applications repositories.   Note that Krzysztof didn't report it on his list, and these components already load them as secrets.   See: \nhttps://git.onap.org/oom/tree/kubernetes/policy/charts/drools/resources/secrets/credentials.conf\nand https://git.onap.org/oom/tree/kubernetes/policy/charts/drools/templates/secrets.yaml.   Besides this, there is another layer that could be added on top of it by the installer where it could encrypt the password, and the encrypted password could be passed as a secret.   Let me know if you want to meet and I can go through the code with you.",
